<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="409" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1654,2003]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="409" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1726,1751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Grimshaw (1901)" authorityName="Grimshaw" authorityYear="1901" box="[342,773,1726,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Sciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molokaiensis">
<emphasis box="[342,568,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Sciara molokaiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grimshaw, P. H." box="[575,773,1726,1751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref15037" refString="Grimshaw, P. H. (1901) Diptera. In: Sharp, D. (Ed.), Fauna Hawaiiensis. 3 (1 - 4). The University Press, Cambridge, pp. 1 - 77." type="book chapter" year="1901">Grimshaw (1901)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was inadequately described on the basis of a single female collected by R.C.L. Perkins in the Moloka‘i Mountains in 
<date box="[816,1003,1762,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" value="1893-09">September 1893</date>
. The female 
<typeStatus box="[1152,1253,1762,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">holotype</typeStatus>
, which we have not studied, is deposited in the BMNH. The re-identification of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grimshaw)" authorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" box="[858,1177,1798,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Sciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molokaiensis">
<emphasis box="[858,1035,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">B. molokaiensis</emphasis>
(Grimshaw)
</taxonomicName>
is discussed by Steffan (1973a: 355). We follow the opinion of Hardy and Steffan that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grimshaw) sensu Hardy" authorityName="sensu Hardy" baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[883,1436,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molokaiensis">
<emphasis box="[883,1140,1834,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Bradysia molokaiensis</emphasis>
(Grimshaw) 
<emphasis box="[1294,1356,1835,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">sensu</emphasis>
Hardy
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Winnertz" authorityYear="1867" box="[386,487,1870,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[386,487,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Bradysia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
near to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tuomikoski, 1960" authorityName="Tuomikoski" authorityYear="1960" box="[577,961,1870,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabricornis">
<emphasis box="[577,747,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">B. scabricornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tuomikoski, R." box="[754,961,1870,1895]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref18057" refString="Tuomikoski, R. (1960) Zur Kenntnis der Sciariden (Dipt.) Finnlands. Annales Zoologici Societatis Zoologicae Botanicae Fennicae &quot; Vanamo &quot;, 21 (4), 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="1960">Tuomikoski, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is characterized by rough flagellomeres with the scape, pedicel and the first flagellomere pale yellowish; hypopygium short haired and with a closed base, an elongate slender gonostylus with 4 (sometimes 5) apical spines, a somewhat wider than long tegmen with a large area of fine teeth, a rather long aedeagus and distinctly toothed claws. The Hawaiian specimens were compared with the 
<typeStatus box="[259,357,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mohrig, 2016" authorityName="Mohrig" authorityYear="2016" box="[405,800,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspercera">
<emphasis box="[405,629,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Bradysia aspercera</emphasis>
Mohrig, 2016
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[879,1106,151,176]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
and they are identical. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grimshaw)" authorityName="sensu Hardy" baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[309,633,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molokaiensis">
<emphasis box="[309,488,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">B. molokaiensis</emphasis>
(Grimshaw)
</taxonomicName>
from Hawai‘i are also conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Skuse, 1890)" authorityName="Skuse" authorityYear="1890" baseAuthorityName="Skuse" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">
<emphasis box="[1097,1344,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Bradysia crassicornis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Skuse, F. A. A." pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="373 - 413" refId="ref17432" refString="Skuse, F. A. A. (1890) Diptera of Australia. Nematocera. - Supplement I. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 2 (5), 373 - 413. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 18643" type="journal article" year="1890">Skuse, 1890</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingRegion box="[435,658,223,248]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[678,784,223,248]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Australia</collectingCountry>
, therefore 
<taxonomicName authority="Mohrig" authorityName="Mohrig" authorityYear="2016" box="[922,1175,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspercera">
<emphasis box="[922,1074,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">B. aspercera</emphasis>
Mohrig
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grimshaw, 1901)" authorityName="sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molokaiensis">
<emphasis box="[1249,1435,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">B. molokaiensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grimshaw, P. H." box="[158,346,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref15037" refString="Grimshaw, P. H. (1901) Diptera. In: Sharp, D. (Ed.), Fauna Hawaiiensis. 3 (1 - 4). The University Press, Cambridge, pp. 1 - 77." type="book chapter" year="1901">Grimshaw, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
are junior synonyms of it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
